comment: Men have oppressed, tormented and tortured women for eons. Till today in India, there are many actual wife beaters who exist. The amount of suppression of women is way greater than anything men have faced by the opposite gender. That being said, I agree with shwetabh on siding with logic and consider everything as a case by case basis. But there is more than that we can do, because the actions of men in the past are now having an equal and opposite reaction in society. Men can do a lot more to support women and uplift them from the years of conditioning of being suppressed. Just suddenly expecting women to be treating everyone as equal can work for those who didn‚Äôt personally face anything in this generation or who can put their emotions aside is only going to work for a small number of women. Those who have suffered as women or seen other women around them suffer (which will be a greater percentage of the population), will care about symbolism and its repercussions on the greater population. Humans are privy to being dominated by their emotions. We are emotional beings. Acting with logic is the smart thing to do for oneself- which  is why shwetabh‚Äôs popularity is rising. But, we can do a lot more to let women know that many men today are not about oppressing women. And this has to be actionable. Not just words. Maybe slowly the larger female population who is sensitive about the issue of symbolism in the media will start to heal and can see that logic is what everyone should operate under.
